---
title: Cherry Balsamic Chicken with Almond Couscous & Roasted Brussels Sprouts
description: Over here, we believe chicken is a canvas, and we like to paint it with allllll the flavors. Tonight’s palette: A saucy coating that includes glossy cherry jam and balsamic pan sauce—because why choose one of these ingredients when you could have both? Add to that a side of almond-studded couscous and roasted Brussels sprouts, and you have yourself a dinner to Remem-brandt (see what we did there?).
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/649aea3dc8e13be2fa91de06-43d3eddc.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64d24b5a7a42584bbbe50762.pdf
servings: 2
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 710 kcal
  fat: 35 g
  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 57 g
  sugar: 18 g
  protein: 42 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 310 mg
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/cherry-balsamic-chicken-64d24b5a7a42584bbbe50762
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(thinly sliced), separating whites from greens.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @sliced almonds{1/2%ounce}; cook, stirring, until lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add garlic, @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}, and a pinch of @salt{}; cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @water{3/4%cup} and cover. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low. Simmer, covered, until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Drain any excess water from #pot{} if necessary.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Toss Brussels sprouts on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

While Brussels sprouts roast, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season generously all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Pour in @balsamic vinegar{5%tsp}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @cherry jam{1}, and @water{1/4%cup}; whisk to combine. Bring to a simmer and cook until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

Stir @butter{1%tbsp} into pot with couscous; season with salt and pepper.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Divide couscous, chicken, and Brussels sprouts between plates. Top chicken with sauce. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165º.